'''Janner''' refers to any [[England|English]] [[person]] born within 10 [[miles]] of the [[sea]]. However, it has come somewhat of a derogatory term and many use it to describe the [[lower classes]] from the city of [[Plymouth]] in south-west [[Devon]].

Most people these days, when refering to a Janner, is no longer refering to its correct definition (someone born near the sea).  But is using it as a derogatory term to describe someone from Plymouth.  The term is widely used (mainly by the student population) in Plymouth to describe a [[chav]] (or burb) from the [[city]].  As a previous version of this artical suggested "Janner is to Plymouth, as [[scouse]] is to [[Liverpool]]."

An example of such use is "I would not like to go out on [[Union Street]] tonight, as there are too many janners there."

